"If everyone had paid attention to this, maybe today's outbreak would not have happened, " Li said.

2,320 words, about 4 minutes to read

Nearly a month after the incident, Wuhan announced the outbreak of the eight "rumors" , by the Chinese CDC chief epidemiologist Zeng Guang, praised as "pre-Zhuge Liang.

One of them, Li Wenliang, an ophthalmologist at Wuhan Central Hospital, told the Beijing News that at 5:43 p.m. on December 30,2019, he mentioned in a group of classmates that "seven SARS cases have been confirmed in the south China fruit and seafood market. ". An hour later, he added in the group, "the latest news is that the coronavirus infection has been confirmed and the virus typing is under way. ". According to the news released by Wuhan Health Care Commission on December 31,2019, some medical institutions have recently found more than one case of pneumonia, which is related to the south China Seafood City. So far, 27 cases have been found, of which 7 cases are in serious condition.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Li Wenliang in the class group released a message screenshot of people infected with coronavirus. Photo courtesy of the respondents

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
December 30,2019, Li Wenliangfa in the university class of the virus detection report. Photo courtesy of the respondents

On January 1,2020, the Wuhan Police issued a notice saying that some netizens had posted and reposted false information on the Internet without verification, causing adverse social impact. The Public Security Bureau, which investigated and verified the case, summoned eight offenders and dealt with them in accordance with the law. Two days later, Li Wenliang received a letter of caution from the police, who concluded that the statement "there were 7 confirmed cases of SARS in the south China fruit and seafood market" was not true.

Although the new pneumonia was not SARS, the content posted by the message was not a complete fabrication, according to an article published on Supreme People's Court on Jan. 28. If the public had listened to this "rumor" at the time, and based on the panic over SARS, had taken measures such as wearing masks, strict disinfection, and avoiding going to the wildlife market, this would have helped us better prevent and control the new type of pneumonia today, could be a blessing. "It is neither legally necessary nor institutionally possible to attempt a legal attack on all information that does not fully conform to the facts, and it may even lead us to attack the rumor as the opposite of the value of legal justice. "

The next day, the Wuhan Police again reported that the eight had not been detained, warned or fined, and that they had been criticized and educated for being particularly minor.

Zeng Guang, chief scientist of the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention, said in an interview that, "These eight people are honorable, they are concerned about the country and the people, and they have some opinions. As public health experts, we want to talk to them and learn from them. "

In an interview with the Beijing News on January 30, Li Wenliang said he did not think he was spreading rumors, but was reminding people to take precautions. "If everyone had paid attention to this, maybe today's outbreak would not have happened, " Li said.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Li Wenliang sick due to overtime and his wife video chat. Photo courtesy of the respondents



"I don't think I'm a rumor. I'm a warning. "

Beijing News: Why are you being admonished by the police?

Li Wenliang: December 30,2019, I made a statement in the university class group, "Wuhan South China fruit and seafood market confirmed 7 cases of SARS. ". After that, the police dismissed what I said as a rumor, and I was reprimanded.

Beijing News: When was the police admonishing?

Li Wenliang: those who were admonished on January 3,2020, went home on the same day. The police did not detain them, warn them or fine them. The other seven were people I didn't know or know what they were doing.

Beijing News: What is the original intention of spreading this news?

Li Wenhua: I was an ophthalmologist at Wuhan Central Hospital. At that time, seven people from the south China fruit and seafood market came to our hospital for treatment and were then quarantined. Initially, tests on the seven men showed they were infected with the SARS coronavirus. I send these messages in the group, to remind everyone and their loved ones to take precautions, I also told everyone in the group, do not pass the news and test report, did not expect that soon (news) was out.

Beijing News: Do you agree with the nature of rumors?

Li Wenliang: I don't think I belong to the rumor, I am reminding everyone to take precautions. In the classmate group released the virus test report, is our hospital colleagues sent me, the report is done by Shenzhen Bgi Technology Co. , Ltd. , seven people were infected with the number of colleagues also told me. An hour after I sent the message, I made further explanation in the class group, I said in our hospital isolation of seven people, confirmed by coronavirus infection, but the type of virus is still divided. If everyone had taken this seriously, we might not have had the outbreak we have today.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan police admonition to Li Wenliang. Photo by interviewee

Suspected of suffering from new type of coronary pneumonia, want to return to first-line work after recovery

Beijing News: When were you infected?

Li Wenliang: On January 8, I saw an 82-year-old woman with acute angle-closure Glaucoma who did not have fever. The next day, the patient developed fever, her symptoms are "double lung ground glass lesion, " a viral pneumonia. Later, the woman was ruled out of common viral infections, Mycoplasma, Chlamydia infection, etc. , but at that time our hospital did not test for a confirmed patient's Kit, so did not give her a confirmed diagnosis. A lot of people didn't care at the time, we didn't have any special precautions, and I got careless when I came into contact with patients. Later, I was hospitalized with a fever and cough on January 12. I now have a suspected case of new type of coronary pneumonia.

Beijing News: How is the situation now?

Li Wenliang: He is being treated in the respiratory and intensive care unit of Wuhan Central Hospital. Breathing difficulties, with Oxygen Tube, can not get up, talk, occasionally look at the phone, typing and communication with others. At first, I was worried, but the doctor would comfort me every day during rounds. Now I have no fever. I am in a better state of mind than the last few days. I believe the hospital and the doctors, I will be cured.

Beijing News: How do you live in isolation these days?

Li Wenliang: Sleep 5 to 6 hours every night, sleep a little during the day, every day the hospital canteen will come to deliver food, that is, Rice, fried vegetables, meat and so on, eat, drink, defecate and urinate in bed. In addition, my family and I would video-chat each other every day, talking through words.

Beijing news: Your doctor's license was revoked?

Li Wenliang: No, my medical license has not been revoked.

Beijing News: How is your family?

Li Wenliang: My parents also developed fever and other symptoms after me. The CT of their lungs showed ground-glass lesions. They are being treated in other hospitals in Wuhan, but they are fine now. The parents, who are in their seventy, don't know much about it, except to say they'll be discharged after two negative nucleic acid tests. My wife is an ophthalmologist at another hospital, and my child is 5 years old. Now the wife lives with the children at her mother-in-law's house.

Beijing News: How has this affected your family and life?

Li Wenliang: being admonished doesn't have a special effect on me. Thank you all for your concern and support. It makes me feel much more relaxed.

Beijing News: What do you want to do after your recovery?

Li Wenliang: After my recovery, I want to return to the first line of work as soon as possible and continue to see a doctor for the patient.

HSINKING newspaper reporter, Liu Mingyang, editor, Zhao Kaidi proofread, Li Lijun
